There are a huge number of Chinese restaurants in the City and Panda Express is not *that* much cheaper than them (unlike other fast food restaurants), but the quality is sorely lacking compared even the average Chinese place in the city.  The white rice was undercooked, the orange chicken wasn't flavorful enough, and even the entrees that I thought were okay weren't particularly well-executed.  Service was fine.  Overall, not recommended since you can find better places in every neighborhood in the city.
